    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Just updating the bug with the content of the hipchat discussion:\n\nA clean solution would be to \n-let widget views have their own `displayed` event. \n-this event would be triggered after the call to `cell.widget_subarea.append(view.$el)` in manager.js. \n\nThen, WidgetView should do `this.on('displayed', function() { this.model.trigger('displayed'); }, this);`\nIn other words, only the display of a WidgetView triggers the model' s 'displayed' event, which is propagated to Python. \n\nFinally, in the widget containers, `this.model.on(\"displayed\")` can then be replaced by `this.on(\"displayed\")`, and `this.child_views[**].model.trigger(\"displayed\");` by `this.child_views[**].trigger(\"displayed\");`.\n"
  }
